<subSubSection id="D29465518754D81AFF3E4E935641FF66" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9A3136DA8754D81AFF3E4E935641FF66" blockId="14.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFF3E4E935539FF2E" bold="true" box="[199,355,152,179]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Distribution:</emphasis>
Western 
<collectingCountry id="E299764A8754D81AFE2A4E935668FF2F" box="[467,562,152,178]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, north to west 
<collectingRegion id="584AF8388754D81AFD1F4E93573DFF2F" box="[742,871,152,178]" country="Ecuador" name="Esmeraldas" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Esmeraldas</collectingRegion>
and in Río Marañon drainage in south Zamora- Chinchipe, and west 
<collectingCountry id="E299764A8754D81AFE7F4EB655E3FF4A" box="[390,441,189,215]" name="Peru" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Peru</collectingCountry>
on Pacific slope from 
<collectingRegion id="584AF8388754D81AFD474EB7574DFF4B" box="[702,791,188,214]" country="Peru" name="Tumbes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Tumbes</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="584AF8388754D81AFCC74EB75726FF4B" box="[830,892,188,214]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Lima</collectingRegion>
, upper Río Marañon valley of Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion id="584AF8388754D81AFA994EB75484FF66" country="Peru" name="Cajamarca" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Cajamarca</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="584AF8388754D81AFEE04EEA55C7FF67" box="[281,413,224,251]" country="Peru" name="La Libertad" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">La Libertad</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="02B52A5F8754D81AFE524EEB5650FF66" box="[427,522,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[170,1423,534,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,525,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Localities in South America of the 245 skin specimens (squares), and 94 voice recordings (circles) of Euscarthmus m. meloryphus (orange), E. meloryphus paulus (yellow), and E. meloryphus fulviceps (red), examined in this study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3936832" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3936832/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Figure 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D29465518754D81AFF3E4F0E51CAFCC3" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9A3136DA8754D81AFF3E4F0E5583FE4F" blockId="14.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFF3E4F0E5567FE82" bold="true" box="[199,317,261,287]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Remarks:</emphasis>
Intraspecific/individual variation in plumage is almost nonexistent. The majority of the specimens have plain light yellow bellies, and the most variable character is the extension of the fulvous/rufous on the head, with individuals having the color restricted to the forehead, and others with the coloration encroaching on the crown. We recommend use of the English name that appears in 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFCD84F7A501BFE16" author="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E." box="[801,1089,368,395]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" pagination="1 - 517" refId="ref8265" refString="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E. (1927) Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands, Part V, Tyrannidae. Field Museum of Natural History Zoological Series, 13, 1 - 517." type="journal article" year="1927">Cory &amp; Hellmayr (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, which perfectly describes the taxon and its main diagnostic character, considering that the head/front color is different from the “tawny” in the crown of the nominate form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A3136DA8754D81AFF3E4FD651CAFCC3" blockId="14.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFF3E4FD65612FE6A" authority="Swainson, 1838" authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1838" box="[199,584,476,503]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lepturus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruficeps">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFF3E4FD655D6FE6A" box="[199,396,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Lepturus ruficeps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFE6D4FD75612FE6A" author="Swainson, W." box="[404,584,476,503]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10709" refString="Swainson, W. (1838) The Natural Arrangement and Relations of the Family of Flycatchers, or Muscicapidae. W. H. Lizars, Edinburgh, 256 pp." type="book" year="1838">Swainson, 1838</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(p. 181, pl. 20) has been considered since the first revisions and catalogues from the description as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFDC34C0B570FFD87" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" box="[570,853,512,538]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meloryphus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFDC34C0B570FFD87" box="[570,853,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Euscarthmus meloryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFC9D4C0A57D7FD87" box="[868,909,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFC6A4C0A50C2FD86" author="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E." box="[915,1176,512,539]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" pagination="1 - 517" refId="ref8265" refString="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E. (1927) Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands, Part V, Tyrannidae. Field Museum of Natural History Zoological Series, 13, 1 - 517." type="journal article" year="1927">Cory &amp; Hellmayr 1927</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFB5A4C0B5165FD86" author="Zimmer, J. T." box="[1187,1343,512,539]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref11334" refString="Zimmer, J. T. (1955) Further notes on Tyrant Flycatchers (Tyrannidae). American Museum Novitates, 1749, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1955">Zimmer 1955</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFAB04C0B5489FDA2" author="Traylor, M. A. Jr." pageId="14" pageNumber="489" pagination="3 - 112" refId="ref10874" refString="Traylor, M. A. Jr. (1979) Subfamily Elaeniinae. In: Traylor, M. A. Jr. (Ed.), Check-list of Birds of the World. Vol. 8. Museum of Comparative Zoology, Cambridge, pp. 3 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1979">Traylor 1979</bibRefCitation>
). Of the several morphological characteristics presented and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFBE84C2F5095FDA2" author="Swainson, W." box="[1041,1231,548,575]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10709" refString="Swainson, W. (1838) The Natural Arrangement and Relations of the Family of Flycatchers, or Muscicapidae. W. H. Lizars, Edinburgh, 256 pp." type="book" year="1838">Swainson (1838)</bibRefCitation>
in his description, some fit with both species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFDB64C4356BBFDFF" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" box="[591,737,584,610]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFDB64C4356BBFDFF" box="[591,737,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Euscarthmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but three define only 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFC254C4250F2FDFE" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[988,1192,585,611]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufomarginatus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFC254C4250F2FDFE" box="[988,1192,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. rufomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (1) “ 
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFB134C435701FD1B" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">the upper plumage is of a light drab-brown, inclining to fulvous on the rump</emphasis>
” (no form of the 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFBD34C665094FD1B" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" box="[1066,1230,620,646]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meloryphus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFBD34C665094FD1B" box="[1066,1230,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. meloryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex presents differences between the color of the rump and the rest of the back, while 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFC464C9A50D1FD36" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[959,1163,657,683]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufomarginatus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFC464C9A50D1FD36" box="[959,1163,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. rufomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does); (2) “ 
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFAF64C9A5615FD53" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">over the eye, and on the lores, is a dirty white stripe</emphasis>
” (absent in the 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFCFD4CBE57F2FD53" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" box="[772,936,692,718]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meloryphus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFCFD4CBE57F2FD53" box="[772,936,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. meloryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, present in 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFB6C4CBE5138FD52" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1173,1378,693,719]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufomarginatus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFB6C4CBE5138FD52" box="[1173,1378,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. rufomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (3) “ 
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFF5D4CD3508AFD6E" box="[164,1232,728,755]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">the under plumage is white, but straw-coloured from the breast, having the sides ferrugineous</emphasis>
” (flanks in the 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFA7D4CD25540FC8B" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meloryphus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFA7D4CD25540FC8B" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. meloryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex are of the same color of the belly, white or light yellow, or at most slightly greyish; ferruginous in 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFF4A4D2A5524FCA6" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[179,382,801,827]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufomarginatus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFF4A4D2A5524FCA6" box="[179,382,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. rufomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Thus, it is clear that 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFD8B4D2A576CFCA6" authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1838" box="[626,822,801,827]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lepturus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruficeps">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFD8B4D2A576CFCA6" box="[626,822,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">Lepturus ruficeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFC094D2A50E1FCA6" baseAuthorityName="Pelzeln" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1008,1211,801,827]" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufomarginatus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFC094D2A50E1FCA6" box="[1008,1211,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. rufomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="5D8E4D598754D81AFAC64D2A54B9FCC3" authorityName="Wied" authorityYear="1831" class="Aves" family="Tyrannidae" genus="Euscarthmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meloryphus">
<emphasis id="A8FAEAC88754D81AFAC64D2A54B9FCC3" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="489">E. meloryphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite all authors having following the erroneous synonymy of 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1F4B2B8754D81AFC3D4D4E5087FCC2" author="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E." box="[964,1245,836,863]" pageId="14" pageNumber="489" pagination="1 - 517" refId="ref8265" refString="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E. (1927) Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands, Part V, Tyrannidae. Field Museum of Natural History Zoological Series, 13, 1 - 517." type="journal article" year="1927">Cory &amp; Hellmayr (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, here corrected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
